Introduction

Base URL: http://restart.local/

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

Authenticating requests

This API is not authenticated.

Cancellation Management

APIs for User & cancellations

List Cancellation Reasons

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://restart.local/api/v1/common/cancallation/reasons" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://restart.local/api/v1/common/cancallation/reasons"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (200):


{
    "success": true,
    "message": "cancellation_reasons_listed",
    "data": [
        {
            "id": "e5cf4a77-93ee-48fd-b889-6dcf4b7041e3",
            "user_type": "user",
            "payment_type": "free",
            "arrival_status": "before",
            "reason": "test-reason",
            "active": 1,
            "created_at": "2020-08-31 18:13:18",
            "updated_at": "2020-08-31 18:13:18",
            "deleted_at": null
        }
    ]
}
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

Request   

GET api/v1/common/cancallation/reasons

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

URL Parameters

arrived   string   

arrived status of the trip request. the value must be after/before Example: sint

APIs for Complaints

GET api/v1/common/ticket-titles

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "http://restart.local/api/v1/common/ticket-titles" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://restart.local/api/v1/common/ticket-titles"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Create Instant Ride

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://restart.local/api/v1/request/create-instant-ride" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"pick_lat\": 1160,
    \"pick_lng\": 3326.9,
    \"vehicle_type\": \"ut\",
    \"payment_opt\": \"1\",
    \"pick_address\": \"omnis\",
    \"drivers\": \"error\",
    \"is_later\": \"1\",
    \"trip_start_time\": \"2025-08-23 13:55:24\",
    \"promocode_id\": \"qui\",
    \"transport_type\": \"sed\",
    \"drop_lat\": 3.03,
    \"drop_lng\": 20529474.7913,
    \"drop_address\": \"officia\",
    \"request_eta_amount\": 2320.8986,
    \"name\": \"sunt\",
    \"mobile\": 278.231205
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://restart.local/api/v1/request/create-instant-ride"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "pick_lat": 1160,
    "pick_lng": 3326.9,
    "vehicle_type": "ut",
    "payment_opt": "1",
    "pick_address": "omnis",
    "drivers": "error",
    "is_later": "1",
    "trip_start_time": "2025-08-23 13:55:24",
    "promocode_id": "qui",
    "transport_type": "sed",
    "drop_lat": 3.03,
    "drop_lng": 20529474.7913,
    "drop_address": "officia",
    "request_eta_amount": 2320.8986,
    "name": "sunt",
    "mobile": 278.231205
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

Upload Driver's Document

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://restart.local/api/v1/driver/upload/documents" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"identify_number\": \"culpa\",
    \"document\": \"quia\",
    \"document_id\": 1,
    \"expiry_date\": \"consequatur\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://restart.local/api/v1/driver/upload/documents"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "identify_number": "culpa",
    "document": "quia",
    "document_id": 1,
    "expiry_date": "consequatur"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (200):


{
    "success": true,
    "message": "success"
}

Request   

POST api/v1/driver/upload/documents

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

identify_number   string  optional  

optional identify number of the document, required sometimes depends on the document Example: culpa

document   image   

document file provided by user Example: quia

document_id   integer   

id of the documents needed uploaded Example: 1

expiry_date   date   

expiry date of the document, the date should be in the format "date_format:Y-m-d H:i:s", eg:2020-08-13 00:00:00 Example: consequatur

    "http://restart.local/api/v1/user/add-favourite-location" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"pick_lat\": 0.0235,
    \"pick_lng\": 82.7934582,
    \"pick_address\": \"debitis\",
    \"drop_lat\": 5632814.76535348,
    \"drop_lng\": 20.3394,
    \"drop_address\": \"voluptate\",
    \"address_name\": \"nisi\",
    \"landmark\": \"voluptates\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://restart.local/api/v1/user/add-favourite-location"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "pick_lat": 0.0235,
    "pick_lng": 82.7934582,
    "pick_address": "debitis",
    "drop_lat": 5632814.76535348,
    "drop_lng": 20.3394,
    "drop_address": "voluptate",
    "address_name": "nisi",
    "landmark": "voluptates"
};

from which device the driver registered Example: ea

vehicle_type   uuid   

vehicle types. listed by types api Example: iste

address   string  optional  

Must be at least 15 characters. Example: qmwrdpbkhuhpthljwxqxalztiwjimkfbusdrbo

postal_code   string  optional  

Must be at least 6 characters. Must not be greater than 6 characters. Example: poyodk

car_color   string   

car color of the driver Example: laudantium

car_number   string   

car number of the driver Example: et

is_company_driver   tinyInt   

value can be 0 or 1. Example: magnam

service_location_id   uuid   

service location of the driver. it can be listed from service location list apis Example: quo

company_key   string  optional  

optional company key of demo Example: voluptatibus

terms_condition   boolean   

it should be 0 or 1 Example: true

refferal_code   string  optional  

optional refferal_code of the another driver Example: consectetur

car_make   string   

car make of the driver Example: aliquid

car_model   string   

car model of the driver Example: et

custom_make   string   

car make of the driver Example: est

custom_model   string   

car model of the driver Example: ea

    \"transport_type\": \"aut\"
}"

    "http://restart.local/api/v1/request/list-packages"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

    "pick_lat": 82,
    "pick_lng": 5596.2,
    "transport_type": "aut"
};

    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

Request   

POST api/v1/request/create

Headers

Content-Type      

Example: application/json

Accept      

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

pick_lat   number   

pikup lat of the user Example: 1.958427898

pick_lng   number   

pikup lng of the user Example: 6484431.3595

vehicle_type   string   

id of zone_type_id Example: quisquam

payment_opt   tinyInteger   

type of ride whther cash or card, wallet('0 => card,1 => cash,2 => wallet) Example: veniam

pick_address   string   

pickup address of the trip request Example: ducimus

drivers   json   

drivers json can be fetch from firebase db Example: nisi

is_later   tinyInteger  optional  

sometimes it represent the schedule rides param must be 1. Example: est

trip_start_time   timestamp  optional  

sometimes it represent the schedule rides param must be datetime format:Y-m-d H:i:s. Example: odio

promocode_id   uuid  optional  

optional id of promo table Example: ipsum

transport_type   string   

Example: eius

drop_lat   number   

drop lat of the user Example: 14981871.4

drop_lng   number   

drop lng of the user Example: 55249.765

drop_address   string   

drop address of the trip request Example: nulla

rental_pack_id   integer  optional  

optional id of package type Example: 1

}"
